ritain.Uncovering the lives of two overlooked figures, The Perils of Interpreting offers a valuable argument for cross-cultural understanding in a better-connected world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2022) 0aTranslating and interpretingxPolitical aspectszChinaxHistoryy18th century. 0aTranslating and interpretingxPolitical aspectszGreat BritainxHistoryy18th century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh  aA Chinese-English Dictionary.  aAbbreviation.  aAlan Sheridan.  aApotheosis.  aAuthor.  aBarbarian.  aBeijing.  aBritish Raj.  aBy Nature.  aChina.  aChinese name.  aCivilisation (TV series).  aColonial empire.  aColonialism.  aConfucianism.  aConurbation.  aCourtier.  aCross-cultural.  aDaoguang Emperor.  aDecision-making.  aDistrust.  aEndemism.  aEnglish name.  aEponym.  aErechtheion.  aErechtheus.  aErichthonius of Athens.  aFarce.  aFinancial crisis.  aForeign language.  aForeign policy.  aGreat power.  aGuangdong.  aGurkha.  aHegemony.  aHephaestus.  aHerodotus.  aHeshen.  aHigh politics.  aHuman.  aIdeology.  aImperialism.  aIntellectual property.  aInternational relations.  aIshtar.  aJacobus.  aJacques Lacan.  aJane Ellen Harrison.  aJean-Paul Sartre.  aJiaqing Emperor.  aKowtow.  aLawrence Wong.  aLecture.  aLin Zexu.  aLiteral translation.  aLysistrata.  aMacartney Embassy.  aMarguerite Yourcenar.  aMarxism.  aMissionary.  aMythology.  aNarcissism.  aNickname.  aObligation.  aPandroseion.  aParthenos (mythology).  aPhidias.  aPoetry.  aPolicy.  aPolitics.  aPrerogative.  aPromiscuity.  aPropylaea.  aPsychoanalysis.  aPublication.  aQianlong Emperor.  aRaw material.  aRobert Morrison (missionary).  aSelf-image.  aSlavery.  aSocial class.  aSocia